item.title: How to pronounce tlingit
item.description: How do you pronounce Tlingit? What does Tlingit mean? The Tlingit (/ˈklɪŋkɪt/ or /ˈtlɪŋɡɪt/; also spelled Tlinkit; Russian: Тлинкиты) are indigenous peoples of the Pacific Northwest Coast of North America. Their language is the Tlingit language (natively Lingít, pronounced [ɬɪ̀nkɪ́tʰ]), in which the name means “People of the Tides”. What is a correct pronunciation? Pronunciation is the way in which a word or a language is spoken. This may refer to generally agreed-upon sequences of sounds used in speaking a given word or language in a specific dialect (“correct pronunciation“) or simply the way a particular individual speaks a word or language.

item.title: Stars in Beauty Masks: Photos
item.description: When it comes to skincare, most products take weeks (or even months!) to start revealing results, but there is one category that offers instant gratification: the face mask. From clays and muds to sheets and patches, five to 30 minutes is usually all you’ll need to start seeing the brightening, toning and calming effects. The immediate satisfaction of the quickies means they are perfect for Sunday self-care or prepping for a big night out, so it is no surprise that celebs love themselves a good face mask.

item.title: Superstore Cast Reflects on Time Capsule Comedy Before Series Finale
item.description: Attention, Cloud 9 shoppers! Superstore is officially closing its doors after six seasons with its series finale airing on Thursday, March 25 — and the cast is just as emotional as viewers. Stars’ Funniest First Jobs “Ben [Feldman] and I text during almost anything. We were texting during the table read and I was like, ‘Are people starting to cry?’ And he’s like, ‘Well, I just did,’” Lauren Ash told Us Weekly and other reporters ahead of the NBC comedy’s finale.

item.title: Why Nicki Minaj Doesnt Want Her Son To Have A Music Career
item.description: After her 2018 album Queen, Nicki Minaj didn't make any more music for a while. It turned out to be her longest hiatus from music. But through her break, the rapper kept making headlines, especially due to her controversial relationship with husband Kenneth Petty. She also kept in touch with her fans via Instagram Live despite having troubles using it. Recently, as she makes her return to music, the Super Bass hitmaker opened up about motherhood and why she doesn't want her son — unofficially named 'Simba' — to follow in her footsteps.
